       <description>This array of bits are mask control bits for comparison of each of the MAC Address bytes. When masked, the MAC does not compare the corresponding byte of received DA or SA with the contents of MAC Address69 high and low registers. Each bit controls the masking of the bytes. You can filter a group of addresses (known as group address filtering) by masking one or more bytes of the address.
